The term "'''galactic community'''" is a phrase that can refer to either:
*The people all over [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].
*Shared values and principles among the primary actors within a galactic system.

The galactic community grew with the growth of technology and discovery of new [[Star system/Legends|systems]] and civilizations. The first notion of galactic community can be considered the [[Infinite Empire/Legends|Infinite Empire]]. With the passing of time, more of them joined or began interaction with the growing [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].

Isolated or undiscovered locations, species and civilizations were not part of the larger galactic community. For example, the Republic and the [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]] were unaware of the existence of each other, until the [[Great Hyperspace War/Legends|Great Hyperspace War]] and the fall of the Empire shortly thereafter.

The [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] were those regions of the galaxy that were not part of the wider galactic community.

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The concept of galactic community is similar to the real-world's [[Wikipedia:International community|international community]].

